This folder contains useful tools for adding content to the game. Below follows each tool and what it does.
Mapgen.py: This tool is your essential texture creator if you wish to use any other shader than the unlit ones (minus the skybox shaders). It is designed to take any standard picture file you pass to it as arguments and convert it into completely useable texture maps you'd slot in for your materials.
Skysplitter.sh: You use this tool with any skybox shader that requires 6 sides or 6 textures. It takes a picture and splits it up into 6 textures perfectly useable and ready to compose your skybox.
Ambpacker.py: This one is used for any materials from ambientcg you wish to use in the game. Its use is a bit more complicated than the others as its designed to work in two ways. The first has you specify both a roughness and a metallic texture that will then get combined into one texture. The second works if you don't need a metallic texture, such as when you want to use wood with your textures, in this case you'd specify only the roughness map and the tool will create a blank, black texture to combine with to create the single texture.
